<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870303-0087 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Waste ManagementSets 2-for-1 Stock SplitAnd Dividend Increase</HL><DD> 03/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WMXDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><DATELINE> OAK BROOK, Ill.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Waste Management Inc. declared a 2-for-1 stock split and increased its quarterly dividend on pre-split shares.    The waste disposal concern raised its dividend to 18 cents a share from 14 cents, payable April 3 to stock of record March 18. The company last split its shares 2-for-1 in December 1985; the new split is payable April 21 to stock of record March 30.    The company, which has about 107 million shares currently outstanding, cited its revenue and earnings growth and the increased price of its stock.    Waste Management shares closed yesterday at $71.25, up $1.75, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading.    For 1986, Waste Management earned $370.9 million, or $3.52 a share, on revenue of $2.02 billion. The earnings included a gain of $234 million related to the public offering of a subsidiary and a net charge of $85.3 million related to restructuring costs.    As reported earlier, Waste Management last week made a tender offer for Columbus, Ohio-based ChemLawn Corp., a lawn care concern, for about $270 million, or $27 a share. </TEXT></DOC>